The three main error sources that may cause unbalances on CT secondary currents during external faults are [3]:

•Tap changing in the power transformer;
•Mismatch between CT currents and relay tap ratings;
•CTs accuracy differences on either side of the transformer bank.

The common methods used to prevent tripping of a transformer due to inrush current are [3]:

•Desensitize the relay during startup;
•Supervise the relay with voltage relays;
•Add time delay;
•Detect magnetizing inrush using the current harmonics.

