 Here, we assume the clusters are distributed only over the azimuth directions, consistent to the measurement results in [35], and summarize the channel parameters as follows:

•Number of clusters \$(N_{{\rm c}})\$;
•Mean AOA of the clusters: \${\bf \Phi}=[\phi_{\rm c}^{(1)}, \ldots, \phi_{\rm c}^{(N_{\rm c})}]\$, with \$\phi_{{\rm c}}^{(i)}\in {\cal A}_{\phi}\$;
•Angle spread of the clusters: \$\Sigma=[\sigma_{\phi}^{(1)}, \ldots, \sigma_{\phi}^{(N_{{\rm c}})}]\$ with \$\sigma_{\phi}^{(i)} \in {\cal A}_{\sigma}\$; where \${\cal A}_{\phi}\$ and \${\cal A}_{\sigma}\$ denote the set of values of \$\phi_{{\rm c}}^{(i)}\$ and \$\sigma_{\phi}^{(i)}\$, respectively.
